The paper focuses on developing an automatic system for selecting attractive thumbnails from videos, which involves analyzing visual quality and aesthetic metrics of video frames and determining relevance to video content through clustering analysis. This suggests that the paper could fall under multiple sub-categories, including multimedia (cs.MM), computer vision (cs.CV), information retrieval (cs.IR), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and machine learning (cs.LG).
